{"/service/ndnp/mimtptc/batch_mimtptc_inkster_ver01/data/sn88063294/00340589130/1945112501/0364.xml":{"full_text":"NOTICE\nTO WORKERS UNEMPLOYED DUE TO\nGENERAL MOTORS LABOR DISPUTE\nThe Michigan Unemployment Compensation Commission has received\nmany inquiries regarding the eligibility for unemployment compensation ben\nefits for workers whose unemployment is caused hy the General Motors Labor\nDispute Therefore, the following statement has hern prepared to explain to\nthese workers their status under the Michigan Unemploymcnt Compensation\nAct and to explain to those workers who are veterans of World War 11 their\nstatus under the Servicemen's Read) ustment Act of 1944\nELIGIBILITY UNDER MICHIGAN UNEMPLOYMENT COMPENSATION ACT\nThe eligibility of any worker** unemployed because of a labor dispute\nis determined under Section 29(c) of the Michigan Unemployment Compen\nsation Act. which reads as follows:\nSee. 29 An individual shall he d tequnhf icd far henefett:\nFor \u00abny week wirh respect tn which\nfit* rmsl ai perrial unemployment is due\nto a stop pace ot work existing because\not a labor dispute tn the establishment\nm which he it or was las' employed:\nPROVIDED. HOWEVER. That no in\ndividual ahall be disqualified under this\nsection if he shall establish that he it\nnot directly involved in such dispute.\nPor the purpose of this section, no in\ndividuals shall he deemed to be directly\ninvolved in a labor dispute unless it is\nestablished\n(I) That, at the time or in the course\n\u00a9i a Labor diapute in the establishment\nin which he was then employed, he shell\nin concert with 1 or more other em\nployees have voluntarily stopped work\ning other than at the direction of his\nemployer, or\n(21 That he is participating in or\nfinancing or direct.y interested m the\nlabor dispute which caused the stonpsge\nof work PROVIDED. HOWEVER.\nThat the payment of regular union dues\nINTERPRETATION BT THE UNEMPLOYMENT COMPENSATION COMMISSION\nThe Commission bar not completed a\nfull investigation of the labor dispute.\nIt .a not possible at thia time to definitely\ninform each worker as to h;s eligibility\nt ghrs for unemployment compensation\nbenelits.\nInformation given to the Comrenron.\nhowever. .i;ii;catea that substantta\u00dfy thre\nlabor dispute Issue involves the wage rate\nof employees Therefore an employee,\neither a union emplovee or non-union em\nployee whose wage rate may be afteettd\nELIGIBILITY OF WORLD WAR II VETERANS AFFECTED BY THE STRIKE\nThe eligibility of a World War II veteran, unemployed because nf\nthe labor dispute, for federal benefits is determined under Section 800(b;\nof the Servicemens Readjustment Act of 1944, wmen reacis as follows:\nSet ti u 0\nCb) A Claimant shall hr disqualified\nfrom receiving an allowance for anv\nweek with reaped to which it it found\nthat his unemployment t due to a stop\npage ot wrork which exists because of\na labor dispute at the factory, establish\nment. or other premises at which he is\nr.r was last employed PROVIDED.\nThat this subsection shall not apply if\nit is shown that\n(11 he is not particpating in or directlv\ninterested in the labor dispute which\ncauses the stoppage of work; and\n(2) he dees not belong to a grade or\nINTERPRETATION BY THE COMMISSION\nDirect interest in n labor dispute provides for disqualification from\nreceiving a readjustment allowance during the l.d>or dispute. Therefore, vet\n\u2022rat whose wage rates may be affected as a r< of tl sputt w-. 11\nbe determined to be- directly interested in the labor dispute and disqualified\nfrom receiving anv readjustment allowance benefits during the period of the\nlabor dispute\nVeterans whose wage rates will not be affected as a result of the labor\ndispute will be determined to be eligible for a readjustment allowance if they\nare not participating in the labor dispute.\nSEPARATIONS PRIOR TO LABOR DISPUTE\nThe labor dispute does not affect the eligibility of empdovees to un\nemployment compensation benefits or to veterans' readjustment allowaiiirft*_j-\u00a3.\n\u2019hr-.- wen kitd ff foi In k <-f p nor t the date on which work stopped\nbecause of the labor dispute.\nWORKERS NOT EMPLOYED BY GENERAL MOTORS CORPORATION\nThe eligibility for unemployment\ncompensation benefits of individuals\nworking tor employers other than\nthe General Motors Corporation who\nare unemploved indirectly because\nof the General Motors Labor Dispute\nwill be eligible for unemployment\n2965 Carpenter\u2014Oetroit\n5459 W. Fort\u2014Oetrott\n14421 E. Jefferson\u2014 Oetrott\n10765 Grand River\u2014Detroit\n6210 Second Bird.\u2014Detroit\n6590 Hurlbut\u2014Detroit\n112 E. Jefferson -Getrod\n3323 Grati*t-Detr\u00bbM\n15933 Grand Hirer\u2014Detroit\n12360 Gratiot\u2014Detroit\n26 West Warren\u2014Detroit\nLOCAL OFFICES\n7435 Cast Jefferson- Detroit\n9111 East Jefferson\u2014Oelroit\n3HO East 7 Milo Rd.\u2014Detroit\n5604 Grood Hlvor\u2014Detroit\n7755 Hamilton\u2014Oetrott\n9974 Grand River\u2014Detroit\n12415 Conant\u2014Detroit\n2600 Junction\u2014Oetroil\n1606 Joseph Campau\u2014Detroit\n11500 Jos. Campao\u2014Mamlramck\n2338 Biddle Avo.\u2014Wyandotte\nTHE MICHIGAN UNEMPLOYMENT\nCOMPENSATION COMMISSION\nshall not'be construed as financing a\nlabor dispute within the meaning ot\nthis subsection, or\n(3j That at any time, there being no\nlabor dispute in rhe establishment or\ndepartment in which he was employed\nhe shall have voluntarily stopped work\ning. other than at the direction of his\nemployer, in sympathy with employees\nin some other establishment or oepan\ntsicnt in which labor dispute was then\nm progress.\n(4) That at ar.y time, there being no\nlabor dispute in the particular estab\nlishment or department or unit m which\nhe was then employed, he shall have\nlei omr unemployed because of a stop\npige of work which w.is directly caused\nin his particular establishment or de\nj artment or unit bv and solely because\noi a stopnage of work doe to a labor\ne*sptrre wtnch was then 